        "1895": {
          "vnum": 1895,
          "name": "A Cavern by the Sea",
          "description": "You stand in a small cavern opening onto a low cliff along the coast near Mareldja. The walls and floor are cut cleanly from the reddish brown stone, and several highly polished patches suggest that the room once served a more prominent role in the city. Long exposure to brine and wind has worn away most of the shine, however, leaving the surfaces in a more natural state. Three archways allow egress: one onto a natural rock shelf to the west, and two others to the east and south. A brown lizard notices you and leaps to the attack! A brown lizard leaps forward and BRUTALLY crushes you. (1) You are almost ready to expire! You panic! You step intrepidly toward your foe and land a fatal blow on a brown lizard! (5) A brown lizard issues a bloodcurdling cry of pain!",
